 Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Recent revival of a traditional name meaning ‘reddish-brown’, which gave rise to the surname <i>Prothero(e)</i> (from <i>ap Rhydderch</i> ‘son of Rhydderch’). Though unrelated, it is commonly Anglicized as <b>Roderick</b>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Rhydderch Ap Bledri was born in 1098, in Llangadog in Kidwelly, Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, King Bledri Ap Cydifor, was 41 and his mother, Clydwen Ferch Gruffudd, was 28. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Elen ferch Lewys. He died in Dyfed, Wales, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1098–":"1098–Surnud","1090–Male":"1090–Surnud","1098–Male":"1098–Surnud","1115–Male":"1115–Surnud","1115–Female":"1115–Surnud","1131–Female":"1131–Surnud","1136–Male":"1136–Surnud","1057–1117":"1057–1117","1070–Female":"1070–Surnud","Abt 1086":"umbes 1086","1117":"1117","1090":"1090","1115":"1115","1136":"1136","1057":"1057","about 1136":"umbes 1136","1098":"1098","1131":"1131","about 1131":"umbes 1131","1070":"1070","Gwynfe, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Gwynfe, Carmarthenshire, Wales","Wales":"Wales","Llangadog Fawr, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Llangadog in Kidwelly, Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Gwynfe, Llangadog Fawr, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Gwynfe, Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Gwynfe, Dyfed, Wales":"Dyfed, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1098–":"1098–Kuollut","1090–Male":"1090–Kuollut","1098–Male":"1098–Kuollut","1115–Male":"1115–Kuollut","1115–Female":"1115–Kuollut","1131–Female":"1131–Kuollut","1136–Male":"1136–Kuollut","1057–1117":"1057–1117","1070–Female":"1070–Kuollut","Abt 1086":"noin 1086","1117":"1117","1090":"1090","1115":"1115","1136":"1136","1057":"1057","about 1136":"noin 1136","1098":"1098","1131":"1131","about 1131":"noin 1131","1070":"1070","Gwynfe, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Gwynfe, Carmarthenshire, Wales","Wales":"Wales","Llangadog Fawr, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Llangadog in Kidwelly, Carmarthenshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Gw